title: American Katie Nageotte goes from near-disaster to POLE VAULT GOLD | Tokyo Olympics | NBC Sports
author: NBC Sports
description:
U.S. champion Katie Nageotte nearly failed to clear her opening height, missing the first two attempts -- but she had only two more misses the rest of the way, clearing 4.90m (16 feet, 1 inch) to outduel Anzhelika Sidorova of the ROC for women's pole vault gold. #NBCOlympics #Tokyo2020 #TrackandField
